 Ahora tenemos que 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F\left(x_{1},...,x_{m}\right)=F\left(x_{1}\right)\cdot...\cdot F\left(x_{m}\right),\ \forall\left(x_{1},...,x_{m}\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{m}
\]

\end_inset

 esto, por la definición de función de distribución, quiere decir que 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P\left(X_{1}\leq x_{1},...,X_{m}\leq x_{m}\right)=P\left(X_{1}\leq x_{1}\right)\cdot...\cdot P\left(X_{m}\leq x_{m}\right)
\]

\end_inset

 Ahora, sea 
\begin_inset Formula $I=\left\{ i_{1},...,i_{k}\right\} \subset\left\{ 1,...,m\right\} $
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $J=\left\{ 1,...,m\right\} \setminus I=\left\{ j_{1},...,j_{l}\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 Entonces, haciendo tender 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{j}\rightarrow\infty,\ \forall j\in J$
\end_inset

, se tiene que
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P\left(\bigcap_{i\in I}X_{i}\leq x_{i}\right)=F\left(x_{i_{1}},...,x_{i_{k}}\right)=\lim_{x_{j}\rightarrow\infty,\ j\in J}F\left(x_{1},...,x_{m}\right)=
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim_{x_{j}\rightarrow\infty,\ j\in J}F\left(x_{1}\right)\cdot...\cdot F\left(x_{m}\right)=\prod_{i\in I}F\left(x_{i}\right)\prod_{j\in J}\lim_{x_{j}\rightarrow\infty}F\left(x_{j}\right)\overset{***}{=}\prod_{i\in I}F\left(x_{i}\right)=\prod_{i\in I}P\left(X_{i}\leq x_{i}\right)
\]

\end_inset

 donde 
\begin_inset Formula $***$
\end_inset

 se debe a que 
\begin_inset Formula $F\left(\infty\right)=1$
\end_inset

.
